==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emollient
<hw>E*mol"lient</hw> <pr>(?; 106)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>emolliens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>emollire</ets>
to soften; <ets>e</ets> out + <ets>mollire</ets> to soften,
<ets>mollis</ets> soft: cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧mollient</ets>. See
<er>Mollify</er>.]</ety> <def>Softening; making supple; acting as an
emollient.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Emollient</xex> applications.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

